Two years since a raft of reforms  introduced  by former education cabinet secretary Dr.Fred Matiang’i, the country has began  reaping the fruits as attested by this year’s KCSE results.
Compared to previous years, the 2018 KCSE results  witnessed a resurgence of  traditionally performing schools like Mang’u High School, Moi High School Kabarak, Maseno and Alliance high school. 